title: Princess
body:
WARNING: Abusive boyfriend. Blood. 

Crap. The last of your makeup had run out once again. It was the third time this week. You knew exactly why. But you also knew that you couldn’t exactly strut out of your room and announce to the world what was going on. Your father would be so disappointed in you. Not because he knew you made the wrong choice. Those things happen sometimes. No, it was because you didn’t come to him.

Your father, the one and only Tony Stark, was a huge softly at heart. He cherishes you and your mother Pepper like he was your own. He wasn’t though and the tabloids always brought that up.

Tony was technically your adopted father. Pepper had legal custody over you when her best friend died in a freak accident with a truck.  So he wasn’t exactly your biological dad, but he was close enough. After all, family doesn’t end with blood. A lesson you learned pretty early on.

You scrambled away from the door as a fist hit it with a bang. You quickly pulled the long sleeves of your Stowe sweatshirt over the black and blue bruises that you usually covered with makeup. This is exactly why you needed more makeup.

Tony would get suspicious if you didn’t were short sleeved shirts in the middle of summer, but, now that it was almost Spring, you could get away with it a lot easier. You gripped the metal door handle before you walked out of the bathroom.

There in front of you was your father sheepishly holding one of his pieces for the newest suit he was building. You turn back to the door where you thought a fist had been brought down. Much to your surprise, it seemed as if he had accidentally run into the door.  

“Hey girlie, sorry about that. Got carried away and everything. You know how I am,” he explains rubbing the back of his neck. It was a nervous reaction he had wherever you or Pepper caught him doing something he shouldn’t have.

You raised an eyebrow.

“Anyways,” he drawled, “The team has a mission that we have to complete before your birthday. Don’t want another 2018,”

You stifled a laugh. Your birthday last year was wild. Apparently Tony had a protocol on his suit in case he was on a mission on your birthday. Let’s just say that this year wouldn’t involve almost burning the house to the ground or anything like that.

“Just come home safe,” You said, hugging him tightly. You were never reassured when he went out on missions. You knew that Friday would keep him safe, but there was always a chance that he wouldn’t come back to you.

“Always do,” He says as he tapped his chest. His suit began to crawl out, the nanotech more advanced than the first time he tested it on your stuffed panda Cosmo.

“Love you,” you whispered, kissing his metal cheek. While your father couldn’t exactly kiss you back, you knew that he would have.

“Love you more,” He said before flying through the window, smashing it to pieces. Not exactly the most convenient exit, but it was Tony Stark. He could replace it whenever he felt like it. Until then, you had a source of fresh air.

You walked away from the shards of broken glass on the ground to get a broom. You didn’t want to cut yourself or anyone else for that matter. It wasn’t until you felt the harsh pants of a much bigger person beat down on your neck that you realized someone was in the room with you.

“What do you think you are doing?” the voice said as its owner gripped your hair in a tight bunch. You didn’t even try to escape this time. You knew it was helpless. You weren’t able to outrun or fight him. He had complete control of your life.

“Please stop,” You whimpered, as he dragged you out of the room. You could only muffle your cries of pain as he pulled harder on your hair. He threw you down on the floor as he reached your room. You stumbled down onto your knees. You watched as he stormed to your closet to grab anything he could use to hear your screams of pain.

Your momma would be screaming at you that you could run as he filed through your clothing. She would have dragged you by the hand to just run. Run somewhere only Tony could find you. He would protect you from this monster.

“Did you hide all your belts, princess?” He asked in a condescending voice. You bit your tongue as a thousand sarcastic responses flooded your head. You finally decided on the best response that probably wouldn’t get you any beatings.

You said nothing.

You slowly crept to the broken window, your knees becoming bloody on the glass that had broken on the floor. You placed a hand over your mouth to try to muffle any stray whimpers as more glass embedded into your legs. You double tapped the bracelet on your wrist and then flung it out the window.

It slowly emitted large blasts of colored light as it hovered just out of reach. You felt your “boyfriend” (if you could even call him that) pick you up off the ground a throw you across the room. You hit the wall with a bang, the noise echoing across the room.

“Get away from my daughter,” a robotic voice said, deadly quiet. You pulled your knees to your chest as the charging of your dad’s repulsers whirled. You felt someone pick you up and bring you out of the room as more people began to crowd your bedroom.

It took about ten minutes before Tony got to you, but, once he did, he wouldn’t let you go. He kept you encased in his arms as Dr. Cho checked all on your bruised. It turned out that you had a few fractured ribs and some cuts in your knees that needed some stitches.

“How did you get here so fast,” You spoke in a soft voice staring at the wall.

“Friday,” He replied. You could tell he had hundreds of question whirling through his brain.

“Did you…?”

“Kill him?” Tony asked, turning towards you. You nodded your head slightly. He let out a sigh before taking your hand in his and intertwining your fingers.

“No, I didn’t. Don’t get me wrong, I really wanted to. I was about to.” He answered, “But your Uncle Steve stopped me. It’s just…Hon, do me two things next time,”

“Yeah?”

“Tell me, okay. I won’t be mad at you. I want you to trust me. You can come to me for anything. Anything at all,”

You nodded your head, feeling the familiar mist of tears shrowd your eyes. He squeezed your hand.

“And the second?” You asked. He turned to you with a small smile on his face.

“The next time you get called princess in a condescending manner, do me a favor. Use your newly appointed powers and punish the poor peasant.”

You walked away from the shards of broken glass on the ground to get a broom. You didn’t want to cut yourself or anyone else for that matter. It wasn’t until you felt the harsh pants of a much bigger person beat down on your neck that you realized someone was in the room with you.

“What do you think you are doing?” the voice said as its owner gripped your hair in a tight bunch. You didn’t even try to escape this time. You knew it was helpless. You weren’t able to outrun or fight him. He had complete control of your life.

“Please stop,” You whimpered, as he dragged you out of the room. You could only muffle your cries of pain as he pulled harder on your hair. He threw you down on the floor as he reached your room. You stumbled down onto your knees. You watched as he stormed to your closet to grab anything he could use to hear your screams of pain.

Your momma would be screaming at you that you could run as he filed through your clothing. She would have dragged you by the hand to just run. Run somewhere only Tony could find you. He would protect you from this monster.

“Did you hide all your belts, princess?” He asked in a condescending voice. You bit your tongue as a thousand sarcastic responses flooded your head. You finally decided on the best response that probably wouldn’t get you any beatings.

You said nothing.

You slowly crept to the broken window, your knees becoming bloody on the glass that had broken on the floor. You placed a hand over your mouth to try to muffle any stray whimpers as more glass embedded into your legs. You double tapped the bracelet on your wrist and then flung it out the window.

It slowly emitted large blasts of colored light as it hovered just out of reach. You felt your “boyfriend” (if you could even call him that) pick you up off the ground a throw you across the room. You hit the wall with a bang, the noise echoing across the room.

“Get away from my daughter,” a robotic voice said, deadly quiet. You pulled your knees to your chest as the charging of your dad’s repulsers whirled. You felt someone pick you up and bring you out of the room as more people began to crowd your bedroom.

It took about ten minutes before Tony got to you, but, once he did, he wouldn’t let you go. He kept you encased in his arms as Dr. Cho checked all on your bruised. It turned out that you had a few fractured ribs and some cuts in your knees that needed some stitches.

“How did you get here so fast,” You spoke in a soft voice staring at the wall.

“Friday,” He replied. You could tell he had hundreds of question whirling through his brain.

“Did you…?”

“Kill him?” Tony asked, turning towards you. You nodded your head slightly. He let out a sigh before taking your hand in his and intertwining your fingers.

“No, I didn’t. Don’t get me wrong, I really wanted to. I was about to.” He answered, “But your Uncle Steve stopped me. It’s just…Hon, do me two things next time,”

“Yeah?”

“Tell me, okay. I won’t be mad at you. I want you to trust me. You can come to me for anything. Anything at all,”

You nodded your head, feeling the familiar mist of tears shrowd your eyes. He squeezed your hand.

“And the second?” You asked. He turned to you with a small smile on his face.

“The next time you get called princess in a condescending manner, do me a favor. Use your newly appointed powers and punish the poor peasant.”

body: I think it’s pretty significant that Tony Stark decided to save a piece of scrap metal that he built and has had since his teenage years despite the fact that he had just lost his entire mansion with all his personal inclusions, blew up all his suits, and threw his arc reactor into the ocean to represent a new beginning. He can rebuild suits, arc reactors, and AIs, but DUM-E is unreplaceable.
